<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="274" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1753</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Minister of Finance states that he cannot give authority to Receiver for
                            collection of internal revenue, and Council of Ministers protest
                            categorically against control of finances as established by us.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>